{{lowercase|title=eNotes}} {{Infobox Website | name = eNotes | logo = File:ENotes logo.png | screenshot = | caption = | url = {{URL|www.enotes.com}} | commercial = Yes | type = Internet Educational Resource | founded = 1998 | headquarters = Seattle, Washington | language = English | current status = Active | alexa = {{DecreasePositive}} 6,428 ({{as of|2015|10|17|alt=October 2015}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url= http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/enotes.com |title= Enotes.com Site Info | publisher= [[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate= 2015-10-18}}</ref> }}
'''eNotes''' is a student and teacher [[educational website]] founded in 1998, that provides material to help students complete homework assignments and study for exams.
Based in [[Seattle|Seattle, Washington]] in the [[United States]], eNotes specializes in [[lesson plan]]s, [[study guides]] and [[literary criticism]]s and is widely cited across the [[World Wide Web|web]]. It also hosts an active homework help portal where students can ask educators academic questions. The Homework Help section has hundreds of thousands of questions with answers.<ref name=WSJ>{{cite news | last = Chaker | first = Anne Marie | title = Do Study Sites Make the Grade? | publisher = Wall Street Journal | date = 2009-04-09 | url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB123923520520403259 | accessdate = 2010-05-08}}</ref>
The website's material mainly focuses on literature and history, though the company offers a variety of different topics within the humanities. A network of over 1,000 [[teachers]] and [[professors]] contributes much of the content.<ref name=techvibes>{{cite news | last = Lewis | first = Rob | title = Back to School for Seattle's eNotes.com | publisher = Techvibes | date = 2008-08-28 | url = https://techvibes.com/2008/08/28/back-to-school-for-seattles-enotes | accessdate = 2010-05-08}}</ref> It is different from other online [[subscription]] education services in that an in-house publishing team edits uploaded works mainly for grammar and formatting.<ref name=mashable>{{cite news | last = Nicole | first = Kristen | title = eNotes Wants to Revolutionize the Learning Process, But Does it Make it Too Easy? | publisher = Mashable | date = 2008-07-10 | url = http://mashable.com/2008/07/10/enotes | accessdate = 2010-05-07}}</ref><ref name=about>{{cite news | title = About eNotes | publisher = eNotes | url = http://www.enotes.com/help/about | accessdate = 2010-05-08}}</ref> With its subscription model, the company bootstrapped its way to profitability and claims about 750 new sign-ups on a weekday during the school year.<ref name=techvibes/> According to internet analytics firm Quantcast.com, the site is accessed by more than 11 million unique visitors each month, making it among the most-visited education properties in the United States.<ref name="quantcast">{{cite web | title = Enotes.com Traffic and Demographic Statistics by Quantcast | work = Quantcast.com | url = http://www.quantcast.com/enotes.com | accessdate = 2015-10-18}}</ref>
