{{Infobox University |name = University of the Frontier |native_name = Universidad de La Frontera |image_name =Universidad de La Frontera.jpg |image_size = 200px |motto = ''Itinerarium mentis ad veritatem'' |established = 1981 |campus = Andres Bello Campus, Medicine Campus |students = 8.500 |affiliations = [[Consejo de Rectores de las Universidades Chilenas|CRUCH]], [[Consorcio de Universidades Estatales de Chile|CUE]] |location = [[Temuco, Chile|Temuco]], [[Chile]] |website = [http://www.ufro.cl/ www.ufro.cl]
}} '''University of the Frontier''' ({{lang-es|Universidad de La Frontera}}) or '''UFRO''' is a university in [[Temuco]] [[Chile]]. It is a derivative university and part of the [[Chilean Traditional Universities]]. UFRO boasts a student body with a variety of abilities and from a variety of backgrounds, many of them are [[Mapuche]] descent.
==Facilities== The university owns a property called [[Rucamanque]], that is used for research, environmental education, and conservation. Rucamanque holds [[old-growth forest|old-growth]] and [[secondary forest|second-growth]] forest.
